```class Solution {
    public int magicalString(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) return 0;
        int[] s = new int[30001];
        s[0] = 1;
        int index = 1, count = 1, ones = 1;
        while (index < n) {
            if (s[index - 1] == 1) {
                s[index++] = 2;
                if (index < n) s[index++] = 1;
            } else {
                s[index++] = 1;
                ones++;
                if (index < n) s[index++] = 2;
            }
        }
        return ones;
    }
}```
